1
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:58,099
You guys alive?

2
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:01,686
I can't hear you!

3
00:01:55,824 --> 00:01:57,742
How would you rate today's gig?

4
00:01:58,827 --> 00:02:00,036
Five hundred.

5
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,497
-Five hundred? That's high!
-Maki rates a three.

6
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:04,290
That's brutal!

7
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,961
-That's hilarious.
-That's so brutal.

8
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:11,464
It was great. Totally great.

9
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:13,049
The audience was on fire.

10
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:19,222
Okay, now let's decide who'll drive today.

11
00:02:20,431 --> 00:02:23,643
-On the count of three, point.
-Point?

12
00:02:23,726 --> 00:02:25,395
-Point on three.
-Okay.

13
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:27,272
-The worst member?
-That's right.

14
00:02:27,355 --> 00:02:28,189
Thought so.

15
00:02:28,898 --> 00:02:30,316
-That'll be easy.
-Oh, shut up.

16
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,985
-That'll be easy.
-Here goes.

17
00:02:33,611 --> 00:02:34,946
-Okay.
-Let's go.

18
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:36,781
-One, two, three!
-One, two, three!

19
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,422
We're the citizens of this country.

20
00:02:55,174 --> 00:02:56,384
The "citizens"?

21
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:58,177
That's right. The citizens.

22
00:02:58,678 --> 00:03:01,681
That's insane. We're all humans.

23
00:03:01,764 --> 00:03:03,516
I wouldn't be so sure.

24
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:07,520
I'm the leader of this team.

25
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:10,523
We made this game.

26
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:14,235
Incidentally,
it was developed by him, Shitara.

27
00:03:14,736 --> 00:03:17,947
But this will be
the first time it'll be played.

28
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,450
We haven't even played it ourselves yet.

29
00:03:22,619 --> 00:03:24,287
In other words,

30
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:27,582
we'll be playing against you,
the citizens, in this game?

31
00:03:27,665 --> 00:03:28,499
That's right.

32
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:33,588
All the face card games are deathmatches
against the citizens of this land.

33
00:03:34,631 --> 00:03:36,507
The team that loses dies.

34
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:38,051
In other words,

35
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:43,514
these games are serious affairs
even for us citizens.

36
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:47,685
Shall we begin?

37
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:51,648
This is the game we are about to play.

38
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:56,027
Difficulty, King of Clubs.

39
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:57,570
Game…

40
00:03:58,863 --> 00:03:59,948
"Osmosis."

41
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,743
"Osmosis."

42
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:23,281
The rules are very simple.

43
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:26,993
There's a two-hour time limit.

44
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,620
We battle each other for points,

45
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:32,790
and the team with the most points
at the end clears the game.

46
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:36,919
Both teams start with 10,000 points each.

47
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:41,257
You'll divide the points
between members before the game starts.

48
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:47,305
They can be divided as you please,
but the least you can start with is 100.

49
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:50,141
Talk it over carefully before you decide.

50
00:05:51,350 --> 00:05:55,271
The amount you start with
is extremely important in this game.

51
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:01,736
Here's how you get points.

52
00:06:02,445 --> 00:06:05,782
There are three ways to get points.

53
00:06:06,407 --> 00:06:07,408
Battles.

54
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:08,993
Items.

55
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:10,703
Base.

56
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:12,080
Wait.

57
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:13,873
Sure. What's your question?

58
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:16,459
This doesn't make any sense at all.

59
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:18,252
Okay.

60
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:20,421
Without an example,
it's probably hard to get.

61
00:06:21,422 --> 00:06:24,258
For now, I've given you
random amounts of points.

62
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:28,763
The number on your wrist is
how many points you have.

63
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:31,599
Let's start with battles.

64
00:06:33,059 --> 00:06:34,227
ARISU 2,000

65
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:36,646
Battles are decided
by how many points you have.

66
00:06:38,689 --> 00:06:42,110
To battle someone,
you just need to touch your opponent.

67
00:06:42,193 --> 00:06:43,027
Hey!

68
00:06:43,611 --> 00:06:44,737
BATTLE

69
00:06:47,990 --> 00:06:49,575
NIRAGI: 2,000 LOSE

70
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:50,576
KYUMA: 3,500 WIN

71
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,245
The person who has more points wins.

72
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:55,706
The winner gets 500 points from the loser.

73
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:56,707
NIRAGI: 2,000 -500 LOSE

74
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:57,834
NIRAGI: 1,500

75
00:06:57,917 --> 00:07:00,461
KYUMA: 3,500 +500 WIN

76
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:02,255
KYUMA: 4,000

77
00:07:02,338 --> 00:07:05,508
There has been a change
in points for both teams.

78
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:13,015
The King of Clubs Team
leads by 1,000 points.

79
00:07:21,983 --> 00:07:23,276
ARISU: 2,000

80
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:26,320
So you don't know
your opponent's points until you battle.

81
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:27,363
Right.

82
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,992
This means battles are fought
without knowing each other's points,

83
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:33,411
so it's a seriously risky fight.

84
00:07:33,911 --> 00:07:37,290
Also, multiple people can fight a battle.

85
00:07:37,915 --> 00:07:38,958
For example…

86
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:42,587
You two, hold hands.

87
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:49,093
What's this?

88
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:51,012
Don't tell me you're blushing.

89
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:05,359
You two make a nice couple.

90
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:10,948
Anyway, when two teammates
are touching one another,

91
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:13,284
they battle with the sum of their points,

92
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:16,287
so they can defeat an opponent
that they can't defeat alone.

93
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:23,628
Then when you win,
you each split the 500 points.

94
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:28,883
Next…

95
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:31,260
The items!

96
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,721
ITEM

97
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:38,893
Hidden somewhere
inside all these containers are six items.

98
00:08:41,812 --> 00:08:42,772
This place is huge!

99
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:45,525
There are only six in this massive arena?

100
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:48,903
You get extra points
when you touch the item.

101
00:08:49,737 --> 00:08:51,614
Now let me explain this.

102
00:08:51,697 --> 00:08:53,199
The key to making a comeback…

103
00:08:54,534 --> 00:08:55,493
is your base.

104
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:01,666
This is your team's base.

105
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:04,210
Ours is on the other side of the arena.

106
00:09:06,754 --> 00:09:09,549
If you touch the opposing team's base,

107
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,260
you'll get 10,000 points.

108
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:13,970
Ten thousand points?

109
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:16,264
That's freaking insane!

110
00:09:16,347 --> 00:09:19,976
That's why you need to leave a keeper
to protect your base.

111
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:25,189
When a player is touching their own base,
they have infinite points.

112
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:26,983
Infinite?

113
00:09:28,609 --> 00:09:30,945
What if you battle someone
with infinite points?

114
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:35,700
Come here a sec.

115
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:54,427
ARISU: 2,250 LOSE
KYUMA: INFINITE WIN

116
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:56,429
The loser loses 10,000 points.

117
00:09:56,512 --> 00:09:58,264
ARISU: -7,750 -10,000

118
00:09:58,347 --> 00:09:59,432
KYUMA: 3,500

119
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:01,100
The winner gains 10,000 points.

120
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:03,311
KYUMA: 3,500 +10,000

121
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:05,354
KYUMA: 13,500

122
00:10:05,938 --> 00:10:07,023
Hold on here!

123
00:10:08,065 --> 00:10:11,986
What if you lose 10,000 points
and go below zero?

124
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:15,781
You die.

125
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:20,828
If you try to touch the other team's base,

126
00:10:20,911 --> 00:10:23,914
but their keeper blocks you
and touches you,

127
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:25,374
you'll lose 10,000 points…

128
00:10:26,834 --> 00:10:27,918
and die.

129
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:31,464
While the other team gets 10,000 points.

130
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:34,008
That's way too risky!

131
00:10:34,091 --> 00:10:36,761
But if you succeed,
you'll come from behind and win.

132
00:10:40,389 --> 00:10:41,307
Incidentally,

133
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:45,436
when players exchange points
from a battle or at the base,

134
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:49,190
they become inactive
and cannot gain or lose points.

135
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:53,527
If an inactive player touches
an opposing team member…

136
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:55,655
INACTIVE

137
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:58,074
…the bracelets give them
a tremendous shock.

138
00:10:58,574 --> 00:11:01,243
It could even knock you out,
so be careful.

139
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:05,831
Once you touch your own base,
you become active again.

140
00:11:10,294 --> 00:11:11,462
Those are the rules.

141
00:11:12,171 --> 00:11:15,007
After you decide how to divide the points,
the game will start.

142
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:22,306
Wait!

143
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:27,895
I'm Arisu.

144
00:11:30,106 --> 00:11:31,023
Kyuma.

145
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:35,486
I want to know something before we begin.

146
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:40,574
If we clear all the games,

147
00:11:43,119 --> 00:11:44,620
can we return to the real world?

148
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:51,377
First of all, what is the "real world"?

149
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:55,673
This "real world" you want to return to…

150
00:11:57,216 --> 00:12:00,636
it seems that you believe
it is the true world.

151
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:03,722
What do you mean by that?

152
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:06,767
When you were there,

153
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:10,020
how many people could you talk to honestly

154
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,815
and deal with truthfully?

155
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:16,444
Vanity and deception.

156
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:20,156
Shit like that falls away quickly here.

157
00:12:22,324 --> 00:12:23,742
When faced with death,

158
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:27,788
that's when you see
the true nature of people.

159
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:35,588
This world is the real world.

160
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:38,549
Games are true conversations.

161
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:45,389
Let's converse with our naked souls
and with all our strength, Arisu!

162
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:48,934
If you want to know the truth,

163
00:12:49,935 --> 00:12:52,146
then battle me with all your might.

164
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:05,451
All right.

165
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:09,580
I'll show you.

166
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:22,384
You know,
that Kyuma dude seems like a nice guy.

167
00:13:23,010 --> 00:13:24,386
He seemed like a normal person.

168
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:27,139
How can a buck-naked nutjob be normal?

169
00:13:27,681 --> 00:13:30,142
This is just another fight to the death
like all the others.

170
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,062
Okay.

171
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:35,439
Let's divide up the points.

172
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:38,817
How will we divide up the 10,000 points?

173
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:42,321
How about in five equal parts?

174
00:13:42,404 --> 00:13:45,074
It's way too basic.
We'll never win that way.

175
00:13:47,910 --> 00:13:49,078
Like Kyuma said,

176
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:50,913
in this game, Osmosis,

177
00:13:51,413 --> 00:13:55,084
the way we divide the points has
a huge impact on who wins.

178
00:13:55,876 --> 00:13:57,336
You got a plan?

179
00:14:04,301 --> 00:14:05,970
DIFFICULTY LEVEL

180
00:14:06,053 --> 00:14:07,930
Game start.

181
00:14:40,921 --> 00:14:41,922
Here's the plan.

182
00:14:42,506 --> 00:14:45,009
The fast runners get
a low number of points

183
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,720
while the slow runners get a lot.

184
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:53,225
Whoever guards the base gets
the least possible number of points.

185
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:59,231
We'll split into pairs with one high-point
and one low-point member.

186
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:02,109
Why did you pair up with me?

187
00:15:02,192 --> 00:15:03,944
I didn't know you liked me so much.

188
00:15:04,028 --> 00:15:06,822
If I have to see you die,
it won't bother me.

189
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:11,994
The benefit of pairing up is
when you touch an opponent for a battle,

190
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:14,663
they can only see
your total number of points.

191
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:18,083
In other words, our opponents won't know
how much each of us has.

192
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:28,594
NIRAGI: 4,700

193
00:15:29,219 --> 00:15:30,596
USAGI: 300

194
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,641
Combined, we've got 5,000 points.

195
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:37,895
When splitting 10,000 points among five,
they wouldn't give 5,000 to one person.

196
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:39,605
Let's fight this guy.

197
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:41,649
I like that attitude.

198
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:50,908
I see.

199
00:15:57,206 --> 00:15:59,333
He must not have had much.

200
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:12,680
Nothing.

201
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:17,726
No, nothing.

202
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:27,903
Why the heck
did you pair up Usagi and Niragi?

203
00:16:28,612 --> 00:16:29,571
It's part of the plan.

204
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:32,116
Did something happen between you?

205
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:33,659
No. It was nothing.

206
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:36,036
Arisu.

207
00:16:37,746 --> 00:16:40,165
If it's something
that'll hinder our teamwork,

208
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:41,750
then shouldn't you talk about it?

209
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:45,170
That's not it. I did it for a reason.

210
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:47,631
Fine. Whatever.

211
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:55,014
That must be it!

212
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:18,454
KUINA: 300 +2,000
ITEM

213
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:20,039
KUINA: 2,300

214
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:22,458
I got 2,000 points!

215
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:24,209
All right!

216
00:17:26,336 --> 00:17:27,421
Yes!

217
00:17:27,504 --> 00:17:30,591
The Player Team obtained an item.

218
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:34,386
The Player Team leads by 2,000 points.

219
00:17:34,470 --> 00:17:36,805
-That's 12,000 points!
-We lead by 2,000!

220
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:41,268
That's a promising start.

221
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,900
Being cautious is boring.

222
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:49,735
Let's try a battle.

223
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:53,822
ARISU: 4,600

224
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:55,824
KUINA: 2,300

225
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:11,507
Let's stay together.

226
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:14,718
It's two-on-one,
so there's no need to panic.

227
00:18:15,302 --> 00:18:16,136
Right.

228
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:23,185
I didn't mean to eavesdrop,
but I couldn't help hearing you.

229
00:18:24,394 --> 00:18:26,271
Did you have a fight
with another team member?

230
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:33,987
Arisu.

231
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:37,825
There's a lot of determination
in your eyes.

232
00:18:39,409 --> 00:18:43,664
They tell me you've faced death many times
and are prepared to sacrifice everything.

233
00:18:44,623 --> 00:18:49,628
So it's strange to me
that you'd let something trouble you now.

234
00:18:54,591 --> 00:18:56,510
Our team was originally a band.

235
00:18:57,719 --> 00:19:02,391
Sometimes we'd fight and argue,
but they still stuck with me.

236
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:06,520
However, there's something
I learned as a leader.

237
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:10,607
You can't just
randomly lead people around.

238
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:15,487
You need to listen to their feelings
and wait for them to come around.

239
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:20,868
When you do that, you'll eventually
come to understand one another.

240
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:28,000
Okay.

241
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:30,085
Let's do this.

242
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:39,386
You could die today, you know?

243
00:19:39,928 --> 00:19:44,016
It's the same for me and my teammates.
Of course, you guys too, Arisu.

244
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:47,019
So let's not have any regrets.

245
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:48,729
If we're going to die,

246
00:19:49,605 --> 00:19:51,732
then I want us to fight bravely
before we die.

247
00:20:06,121 --> 00:20:06,997
Arisu…

248
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:10,626
Kyuma.

249
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:13,212
Like you said before,

250
00:20:14,129 --> 00:20:18,258
if I want to know the truth,
then I should fight with all my might.

251
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:20,219
Right.

252
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:24,431
I want to start
by getting to know you better.

253
00:20:25,891 --> 00:20:27,392
So battle me.

254
00:20:33,857 --> 00:20:34,858
But Arisu…

255
00:20:39,196 --> 00:20:40,489
With pleasure.

256
00:20:54,836 --> 00:20:57,673
ARISU: 4,600 WIN
KYUMA: 2,000 LOSE

257
00:20:57,756 --> 00:20:58,882
Damn!

258
00:20:58,966 --> 00:21:00,259
There has been a change in points

259
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:01,551
-I lost!
-for both teams.

260
00:21:02,135 --> 00:21:03,053
Two thousand points?

261
00:21:03,136 --> 00:21:04,471
ARISU: 4,600 +500
KYUMA: 2,000 -500

262
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:07,391
The Player Team leads by 3,000 points.

263
00:21:10,894 --> 00:21:14,273
